subsection.def:
judgment
                        (判決) includes any judgment, order and
                    allocatur in civil or commercial matters;

paragraph.content:
no fresh evidence (other than evidence as to matters which occurred
                        after the date of the master’s order) shall be admitted except on special
                        grounds;

where that person is a corporation, with the leave of the Court, a writ
                        of sequestration against the property of any director or other officer of
                        the corporation;

where any change has taken place, whether by death or otherwise, in the
                        parties entitled or liable to execution under the judgment or
                        order;

where under the judgment or order any person is entitled to relief
                        subject to the fulfilment of any condition which it is alleged has been
                        fulfilled;

stating, where the case falls within rule 2(1)(b), the
                        change which has taken place in the parties entitled or liable to execution
                        since the date of the judgment or order;

stating, where the case falls within rule 2(1)(c) or (d),
                        that a demand to satisfy the judgment or order was made on the person liable
                        to satisfy it and that he has refused or failed to do so;

subparagraph.content:
where the writ may not issue without the leave of the Court, the
                            order granting such leave or evidence of the granting of it;
                            and

subsection.content:
Upon appearance of the judgment debtor for examination, he shall give
                    evidence and he may be examined on oath by the judgment creditor and the Court;
                    and the Court may receive such other evidence as it thinks fit.

subparagraph.content:
in the case of stock of any body incorporated outside Hong Kong,
                            being stock registered in a register kept in Hong Kong, on the keeper of
                            the register;

in the case of units of any unit trust in respect of which a
                            register of unit holders is kept in Hong Kong, on the keeper of the
                            register;

paragraph.content:
an affidavit identifying the securities in question and describing his
                        interest therein by reference to the document under which it arises;
                        and

in the case of an appeal from a judgment, order or decision of a master
                        under paragraph (2), 28 days from the date of the judgment, order or
                        decision;

in the case of an appeal from a judgment, order or decision (other than
                        an interlocutory judgment, order or decision) of a judge, 28 days from the
                        date of the judgment, order or decision;

an order striking out an action or other proceedings or a pleading or
                        any part of a pleading under Order 18, rule 19 or under the
                        inherent jurisdiction of the Court;

a judgment or order made under Order 14A, rule 1(2)
                        dismissing any cause or matter upon determination of a question of law or
                        construction of any document;

